<Layout title="Building on Ubuntu" lang="en">
  <h1>Building Live Background Removal Lite on Ubuntu</h1>
  <p>
    To build Live Background Removal Lite on Ubuntu, install all required dependencies using <code>apt</code> and follow the steps below. <strong>Do not use vcpkg.</strong>
  </p>
  <h2>Steps</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Install build tools and dependencies:</strong>
      <pre><code>sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake git pkg-config \
  libopencv-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev libfmt-dev libssl-dev \
  qtbase5-dev qtbase5-private-dev qtchooser qt5-qmake qtbase5-dev-tools \
  libqt5svg5-dev libqt5widgets5 libqt5gui5 libqt5core5a \
  libwolfssl-dev libstb-dev libgtest-dev libgmock-dev
</code></pre>
      <p>
        If you are building for Ubuntu 22.04 or later, you may need to adjust package names for Qt6.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Clone the repository:</strong>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/kaito-tokyo/live-backgroundremoval-lite.git
cd live-backgroundremoval-lite</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Configure the build:</strong>
      <pre><code>cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Build the plugin:</strong>
      <pre><code>cmake --build build --parallel</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Install the plugin:</strong>
      <pre><code>sudo cp -r build/live-backgroundremoval-lite.plugin /usr/lib/obs-plugins/</code></pre>
      <p>
        Adjust the destination path if your OBS installation uses a different plugin directory.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Restart OBS Studio</strong> to load the plugin.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    For more details, see the <a href={BASE_URL + "CONTRIBUTING.md"}>contribution guide</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
